GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 855
Short Title: Residency Licenses for Nonpublic EC Teachers. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Blackwell, Biggs, Lofton, and Scott (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Education - K-12, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 10, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ALLOW NONPUBLIC SCHOOLS TO REQUEST RESIDENCY LICENSES
3 FOR TEACHERS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 115C-270.20(a) reads as rewritten:
6 "(a) Teacher Licenses. – The State Board shall adopt rules for the issuance of the following
7 classes of teacher licenses, including required levels of preparation for each classification:
8 …
9 (5) Residency License or RL. – A one-year license, renewable twice, that meets
10 both of the following requirements:
11 a. Is requested by the governing body of a public school unit and
12 accompanied by a certification of supervision from the recognized
13 educator preparation program in which the individual is enrolled.either
14 of the following entities and is accompanied by a certification of
15 supervision from the recognized educator preparation program in
16 which the individual is enrolled:
17 1. The governing body of a public school unit.
18 2. A nonpublic school that meets the requirements of Part 1 or
19 Part 2 of Article 39 of this Chapter.
20 3. A nonpublic school approved and monitored by the
21 Department of Public Instruction that provides services for
22 students with extraordinary costs. For the purposes of this
23 subsection, extraordinary costs shall include costs directly
24 attributable to providing the special education services on the
25 student's IEP.
26 b. The individual for whom the license is requested meets all of the
27 following requirements:
28 1. Holds at least one of the following:
29 I. A bachelor's degree.
30 II. An advanced degree.
31 2. Has either completed coursework relevant to the requested
32 licensure area or passed the content area examination relevant
33 to the requested licensure area that has been approved by the
34 State Board.
35 3. Is enrolled in a recognized educator preparation program.
*H855-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 4. Meets all other requirements established by the State Board,
2 including completing preservice requirements prior to
3 teaching.
4 …."
5 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies to applications
6 for residency licenses occurring on or after that date.
